A version 0.11
==============

NAME

ShiftJIS::Regexp - to use Shift_JIS-oriented regexps in the byte-oriented perl.

SYNOPSIS

  use ShiftJIS::Regexp qw(:all);
  match('‚ ‚¨‚P‚Q', '\p{InHiragana}{2}\p{IsDigit}{2}');
  match('‚ ‚¢‚¢‚¤‚¤‚¤', '^‚ ‚¢+‚¤{3}$');
  replace($str, 'A', '‚`', 'g');

DESCRIPTION

This module provides some functions to use Shift_JIS-oriented
regexps in the byte-oriented perl.

  re() returns Shift_JIS-oriented regexps parsable by the byte-oriented perl.
  match() works like m///.
  replace() works like s///.
  jsplit() works like CORE::split.

INSTALLATION

To install this module type the following:

   perl Makefile.PL
   make
   make test
   make install

PREREQUISITES

perl.

